<ue5><m0>Quebec leaders worry riot may hurt tourism<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>QUEBEC <m0>(--) Some Quebec City officials wondered Monday whether the city's tourism industry is about to take a hit after a weekend riot.<ep>
   ``It's true that it gives us a bad image,'' Acting Mayor Claude Cantin said. ``But I hope we can remake our image in tourists' eyes.''<ep>
   Cantin was particularly worried that pictures of youths hurling bottles and rocks were broadcast over the weekend on CNN, the U.S. cable news network.<ep>
   Between 1,000 and 1,500 people clashed with police on the edge of the city's historic old quarter late Saturday night. It took police using tear gas and pepper spray about three hours to disperse the crowd.<ep>
   Sixteen arrests were made and eight police officers were injured by flying debris. Windows in about 15 stores and restaurants were smashed and several cars were also damaged.<ql>
