<ue5><m0>Judge: Olympians can don designer duds<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>TORONTO <m0>(--) Canada's Olympic athletes will have designer clothes on their backs after all at this summer's games in Atlanta.<ep>
   A Federal Court judge refused Monday to grant an injunction preventing the athletes from wearing outfits for the Olympics' opening and closing ceremonies that have been credited to designer James Yunker of Toronto.<ep>
   Another Toronto designer, Hasmig Possian, had sought the injunction, saying the designs resemble sketches she had submitted well before Yunker's drawings were selected in June 1995.<ql>
