<ue5><m0>Municipal Financial to sell trust to bank<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>BARRIE, Ont <m0>.(--) Municipal Financial said Monday it agreed to sell its Municipal Trust Co. division and other assets to National Bank of Canada for about $46 million Canadian, or U.S. $34 million.<ep>
   The sale includes Municipal Financial's regulated subsidiaries (--) Municipal Trust, Municipal Savings & Loan, MSL Properties Ltd. and Municipal Securities. Municipal Trust has 29 branches in southern Ontario.<ep>
   Completion of the deal is subject to certain conditions, including the sale of Municipal Financial's leasing division to a third party on terms satisfactory to National Bank. The transaction is expected to close by Aug. 15.<ql>
