<ue5><m0>Couple arrested after children beg for money<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0> <m0>MONTREAL <m0>(--) Police arrested a French couple over the weekend and placed their three children in protective custody after the man and woman allegedly made the kids beg for money in historic Old Montreal.<ep>
   The parents were later released because begging for money isn't a crime in Montreal, police said.<ep>
   The parents, who weren't named to protect the children, ages 6, 8 and 9, claim they've done nothing wrong.<ep>
   The family is from Nancy, in eastern France, and arrived in Canada with their two daughters and son March 21. They told the newspaper they'd like to move to the French islands of Saint-Pierre-et-Miquelon, near Newfoundland.<ep>
   Police arrested the man Saturday in Old Montreal with two of his children. The mother was arrested later with the third child in a small hotel.<ql>
